column4: "This item can't be printed because it is not a contiguous shape.  The letters are floating a couple of millimeters above the base.  Our 3D printer builds from the ground up, so if you'd like the letters to be standing on the base, they must actually be attached to it, otherwise they'll be printed on supports that are designed to be breakable for easy detachment, meaning the whole thing will likely fall apart.  We are unable to fix or alter models for you, unfortunately, so I'm denying this request; but you're welcome to edit your model and resubmit it."

column54: "Haley - The submitted model was not not symmetrical, so we were not able to size it to 10"" x 10"". The size of the model is 254mm x 245.63mm (254mm = 10""). For future reference, it is best to submit a print a minimum of one week in advance of any deadline. If the print is larger or more complex, an even larger amount of lead time might be needed. This lead time is often necessary due to the large number of submissions we receive, long print times, printer malfunctions, difficult to print models, and various other factors. Thank you for your understanding."
